        <p>Converts the cursor to Bubble mode, which lets you create a callout by clicking in the image and dragging a rectangle area. When you release the cursor, a "bubble" shape is created, which consists of a rectangular or square area for holding text and a pointy area for pointing toward an area of the image that you want to explain or emphasize. See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../Capture/Interface/Dialogs/Bubble-Properties-Dialog.htm" target="" title="" alt="">Bubble Properties Dialog</MadCap:xref>.</p>
